• Ties with China are in a downward spiral after Mr Trump engaged the economic superpower in what is dubbed a new Cold War.
Mr Biden has pledged to work more closely with US allies in confrontin­g China on trade, and is unlikely to roll back Mr Trump’s tariffs on Chinese goods any time soon. Russia
Take a tougher approach to Russia and President Vladimir Putin, with whom Mr Trump has long faced scrutiny over their warm relationsh­ip. Mr Biden might seek to extend sanctions against Russia over its annexation of Ukraine’s Crimean peninsula in 2014. Europe Repair relations with the European Union, which Mr Trump has often disparaged. Iran • Stimulus package to assist families and small businesses. Free vaccine and testing. Increase supply of personal protective equipment. A blueprint that will start on Jan 20 Rejoin World Health Organisati­on which Mr Trump had sought to withdraw from with effect from July 6 next year after accusing the body of favouring China. ECONOMIC RECOVERY US$1.3 trillion infrastruc­ture investment. Raise minimum wage to US$15 an hour Tax hikes on the rich and corporatio­ns. ‘Buy American’ policy meant to boost US domestic manufactur­ing. Create millions of new good-paying jobs with a choice to join a union. CLIMATE AND ENERGY CORONAVIRU­S PANDEMIC FOREIGN POLICY
